#compdef git-igitt
# =============================================================================
# git-igitt — Martin Lange's "Interactive Git terminal application to
#             browse and visualize Git history graphs arranged for
#             your branching model" — a Rust TUI wrapping git2-rs
#             with crossterm + tui-rs (now ratatui's predecessor).
#             Distinguishing from tig, gitui, lazygit, gitlinks, and
#             other terminal Git browsers by:
#               - BRANCHING-MODEL-AWARE GRAPH RENDERING: built on
#                 the `gleisbau` library (also by Martin Lange) which
#                 computes Git history graphs ARRANGED ACCORDING TO
#                 BRANCHING MODELS (simple/git-flow/none); commits
#                 are laid out in the graph such that branches flow
#                 in canonical directions for the chosen model
#               - PER-REPOSITORY MODEL OVERRIDE: `git-graph.toml`
#                 (per-repo config) + `git-igitt model <name>`
#                 subcommand sets the branching model PERMANENTLY
#                 for a given repository
#               - 5 BOX-DRAWING STYLES: --style {normal|thin|round
#                 |bold|double|ascii} for the connecting lines in
#                 the graph; first-letter abbreviation accepted
#               - 5 COMMIT FORMATS: --format {oneline|short|medium
#                 |full|"<custom>"} with custom-string placeholders
#                 (see git-graph)
#               - SPARSE MODE (--sparse): merge lines point to
#                 target lines rather than merge commits; produces
#                 a less dense but more readable graph
#               - LOG-LEVEL FILE OUTPUT (--log-level): writes
#                 log.txt with configurable level (error/warn/info/
#                 debug/trace/off); used for troubleshooting
#                 graph-layout issues
#               - log4rs FILE APPENDER: every log message routed
#                 through a log4rs::append::file::FileAppender with
#                 PatternEncoder formatting; LevelFilter set
#                 dynamically based on --log-level flag value
#             Used by: developers working with complex branching
#             workflows (git-flow, GitHub Flow, Trunk-Based) who
#             want a TUI alternative to `gitk --all` with model-
#             aware graph arrangement.
#
# Author:  Martin Lange (martin_lange_@gmx.net, mlange-42 +
#          git-bahn on GitHub) — German Rust developer who built
#          the `git-graph` CLI + `git-igitt` TUI + `gleisbau`
#          library trio.  Continuous development through 2026
#          with versioned releases (0.1.21 at time of writing).
# Source:  https://github.com/git-bahn/git-igitt
#          https://github.com/git-bahn/git-igitt/blob/master/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/git-bahn/git-igitt/blob/master/Cargo.toml
# CLI:     src/main.rs — uses clap 4.x builder API with Arg::new()
#          + .long() + .short() + .help() + num_args().  Headline
#          library: **log4rs** (clap is well-documented across many
#          Rust completions — log4rs is the new variant being
#          documented here).
# Library: log4rs (https://github.com/estk/log4rs)
#          ("log4rs" — Steven Allen (estk on GitHub) — released
#           2015 as a Rust port of Java's log4j logging framework.
#           Distinct from env_logger (R582), slog (R586), tracing
#           (R590), fern (R594), and simplelog (R606) by being:
#             1. XML/YAML/JSON-CONFIG-DRIVEN — log4rs loads its
#                ENTIRE configuration from a config FILE at runtime
#                (or programmatically) — appenders, encoders,
#                loggers, root logger, level filters, all declared
#                as data
#             2. APPENDER ABSTRACTION — output destinations
#                ("appenders") are pluggable: ConsoleAppender,
#                FileAppender, RollingFileAppender, AsyncAppender,
#                + custom appenders via the Append trait
#             3. ENCODER/PATTERN ABSTRACTION — output formatting
#                via PatternEncoder with log4j-style format string
#                placeholders: {d} date, {l} level, {t} target,
#                {m} message, {n} newline, {f} file, {L} line,
#                {T} thread, {X(...)} MDC value
#             4. ROLLING FILE APPENDER — built-in log rotation
#                with size-based, time-based, or hybrid triggers +
#                file-archival rollers (with optional gzip
#                compression)
#             5. LOG4J HERITAGE — appender names, configuration
#                schema, and pattern-encoder syntax mirror log4j +
#                logback exactly; Rust developers coming from JVM
#                find the API immediately familiar
#             6. RUNTIME RECONFIGURATION via the Handle returned
#                from init_config() — can swap entire logger
#                config at runtime by calling Handle::set_config()
#             7. THREAD-SAFE + ASYNC APPENDER for log forwarding
#                without blocking the calling thread on slow
#                appenders (e.g. network or database backends))
# License: MIT OR Apache-2.0 (git-igitt + log4rs)
# Status:  git-igitt — 265+ stars on git-bahn/git-igitt; log4rs —
#          1,200+ stars on estk/log4rs, ~60M crates.io downloads,
#          foundational dependency of autozimu/LanguageClient-
#          neovim (3.5k stars) + sytsereitsma/mdbook-plantuml +
#          purefinance/mmb (trading bot) + tickbh/wmproxy (web
#          proxy) + git-bahn/git-igitt (THIS) + h26forge/h26forge
#          + 400+ Rust services that prefer XML/YAML-config-driven
